Would you considered doing a video tag for healthcare workers? For months I gave up makeup because of having to wear PPE at work. I'm an ICU Nurse and work 12 hour shifts. I live in Florida and have oily eyelids. My holy grails are Dior's waterproof mascara and Colourpop's s Sweet talk palette. I've been pretty uninspired until recently when I cleaned out my makeup.  I also started relaxing again.. by watching makeup tutorials. I pretty much accept my face makeup is going to wear off because of wearing masks....but what about eyes? I'd like to see products and  techniques that last. (or atleast fade nicely.) I love Goth and Rockchick looks but don't want makeup all over my face by the end shift. I think a lot of people would love this topic. I love the looks you come up with. Just trying to find new ways to take back my pre epidemic enjoyment..Thanks Mikki ♡
